            <h1>About Kaziranga National Park</h1>
            <p>
                Kaziranga National Park is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in the Indian state of Assam. 
                It is famous for being home to the world's largest population of the Indian one-horned rhinoceros. 
                Spanning over 800 square kilometers, the park features a rich ecosystem of tall grasslands, marshes, and tropical forests.
            </p>
            <p>
                Apart from rhinos, Kaziranga also shelters tigers, elephants, wild water buffalo, swamp deer, and many species of birds. 
                The park is divided into several ranges and offers safari rides, eco-resorts, and educational experiences for nature lovers. 
                It plays a crucial role in wildlife conservation and biodiversity in India.
            </p>
